modules.description: Processes OCaml source code to apply syntax highlighting, using a customized lexer that strips docstrings and simplifies error handling. Operates on strings representing OCaml code and outputs formatted results suitable for web display. Used to integrate syntax highlighting into web-based OCaml editors or viewers built with js_of_ocaml and brr.

Lexes OCaml source strings into annotated token lists, where each token includes its content and a tag for styling. Processes HTML-escaped strings by converting entities back to their original characters. Used to generate styled HTML elements from OCaml code snippets in web applications.
